<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12137m"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12137m">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12137m"> 137(m)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Celt, red harness / necklace</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The <mark>Celts</mark> <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> borrowed from the Greeks the practice of making <mark>red</mark> enamel, originally invented by the Egyptians <font color="green">[who had used red coral]</font>, and continued, down to the time of their conversion to Christianity, to adorn their <mark>harness</mark> and armour, and to make their <mark>necklaces</mark>, of red enamel, in place of red coral. <small> William James Perry, <a name="ORMR" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ORMR"><cite title="source">Origin of Magic and Religion</cite></a> (1923) 13</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c12141h" href="c12all.htm#c12141h">VI.C.12:141(h)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
